 A 200-level student of Management and Accounting Department in Obafemi Awolowo University, Ile-Ife, Osun State, Emmanuel Adedeji, has committed suicide. The Nation gathered that Adedeji ingested poisonous substance, an insecticide, on the school premises and died a few minutes later.  A student of the institution, Bukola Adewumi told our correspondent that his body was discovered behind the Mechanical Department popularly known as Spider building. The institution’s spokesman Abiodun Olarewaju confirmed the incident, appealing to “parents and guardians to please let their children know” that suicide is not an option in a case of “failure or depression”. 